<p>Angular contains validation classes </p>
<ul>
    <li>.ng-valid: Applied when the form control is valid.</li>
    <li>.ng-invalid: Applied when the form control is invalid.</li>
    <li>.ng-touched: Applied when the form control has been touched (focused and then blurred).</li>
    <li>.ng-untouched: Applied when the form control has not been touched.</li>
    <li>.ng-dirty: Applied when the form control's value has been changed.</li>
    <li>.ng-pristine: Applied when the form control's value has not been changed
</ul>
 
 
